Re: colloquial Japanese
by furrykef » Tue 09.01.2009 9:52 pm A lot of guides (such as Tae Kim's) cover some colloquialisms, but perhaps the best way to get acquainted with it would be to watch Japanese TV (anime would probably not be the best example unless you're careful to figure out what sorts of stuff people say in anime but not in real life).
Founder of Learning Languages Through Video Games.Also see my lang-8 journal, where you can help me practice Japanese (and Spanish, and Italian!)
