Re: colloquial Japanese
by furrykef » Tue 09.01.2009 10:10 pm Ugh. I wouldn't consider text-speak, l33t-sp33k, etc. to be colloquial English; why would it be colloquial Japanese? (OK, technicially it is colloquial speech, but when somebody says "I want to learn colloquial speech", they usually don't mean "d00d im sk8tn". )
