by keatonatron » Wed 09.02.2009 8:03 am furrykef wrote:Ugh. I wouldn't consider text-speak, l33t-sp33k, etc. to be colloquial English; why would it be colloquial Japanese? Because Japanese people don't use text-speak.They simply write informally (and quite close to how they actually talk) when conversing on the internet.
